sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.author_id)
FROM Author a
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN Citation c ON al.paper_id = c.cited_paper_id
    WHERE al.author_id = a.author_id
    GROUP BY al.paper_id
    HAVING COUNT(c.paper_id) > 50
)
question: Find the number of authors who did not publish any paper that is cited more than 50 times.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT author_id)
FROM Author_list
WHERE author_id NOT IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT al.author_id
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN (
        SELECT cited_paper_id
        FROM Citation
        GROUP BY cited_paper_id
        HAVING COUNT(*) > 50
    ) c ON al.paper_id = c.cited_paper_id
)

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.author_id) AS num_authors_no_highly_cited_paper
FROM Author a
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN Citation c ON al.paper_id = c.cited_paper_id
    WHERE al.author_id = a.author_id
    GROUP BY al.paper_id
    HAVING COUNT(c.paper_id) > 50
)
question: Find the number of authors who did not publish any paper that is cited more than 50 times.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.author_id) AS num_authors_no_highly_cited_paper
FROM Author a
WHERE a.author_id NOT IN (
    SELECT al.author_id
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN (
        SELECT c.cited_paper_id, COUNT(*) AS citation_count
        FROM Citation c
        GROUP BY c.cited_paper_id
        HAVING COUNT(*) > 50
    ) high_cited ON al.paper_id = high_cited.cited_paper_id
)
